--- B.1: PV->PIII parameter-space degeneration prescription

FW S4 prose at .txt L3905-3911 describes PV->PIII as a
hard-edge scaling COORDINATE-SPACE limit (eigenvalue spacing
scaling). The PARAMETER-SPACE prescription mapping
(v_1, v_2, v_3, v_4) -> (v_1, v_2) is NOT given verbatim in
FW S4.1; FW just postulates the PIII Hamiltonian (4.1) with
two surviving parameters, citing Okamoto [31] (Okamoto 1987).

Implicit FW prescription (anchored by S2.1 vs S4.1 coefficient
match in okamoto_substrate_extract.txt note 109-O2):
  The FW PIII' form (4.1) hardcodes eta_inf = eta_0 = 1
  in the q^2 p and t p coefficients respectively.
  The PV (2.1) form contains the four v_i without WLOG.
  Going PV->PIII means *integrating out* the v_3 and v_4
  dependence by sending the difference (v_3 - v_4) to the
  hard-edge limit: see FW (2.5) where alpha = (1/2)(v_3-v_4)^2
  is the *only* place v_3, v_4 enter the PV ODE coefficients
  beyond combinations that absorb into Okamoto's (theta_0,
  theta_inf) on the PIII side.

